<p class="">The hon. Gentleman was making the point, not that it had not been proposed, but that it had not been ratified. The hon. Member made the point that to propose talks now would be a sign of great weakness. <em>A fortiori</em>, it would have been equally weak if Western European defence had not been conceived and was not there at all.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
